title.narrative: Upgrading and Greening the Rio de Janeiro Urban Rail System

description.narrative: (a) to improve the level of service provided to suburban rail transport users in the RJMR in a safe and cost-efficient manner; (b) to place the suburban rail transport system on a lower carbon growth path; and (c) to improve the transport management and policy framework in the Borrower's territory and in the RJMR.

condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :IBRD-77190 | Description :State of Rio de Janeiro/SETRANS must maintain throughout the project a ProjectManagement Unit. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :IBRD-77190 | Description :The State shall, within the limits of its authority, commit to preserve AMTU-RJ and tointroduce and maintain a type of Integrated Modal Tariff (IMT) during execution of the projec | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I.A.1 | Description :The Borrower, through SETRANS, should maintain a Project ManagementUnit with staff, responsibilities, structure and functions satisfactory to the Bank. | Frequency :Yearly
Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I.A.2 | Description :The Subsidiary Agreement between SETRANS and CENTRAl is maintainedthroughout duration of project. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I.C | Description :The Borrower, through SETRANS, shall carry out, and shall cause CENTRALand the Concessionaire to carry out, the Project in accordance with the provisions and recommendations of the EMP and RAP. |Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section II.A.1 | Description :The Borrower through SETRANS shall cause CENTRAL to monitor andevaluate the progress of the Project and furnish to the Bank Project Reports. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section II.B | Description :The Borrower, through SETRANS, shall cause CENTRAL to maintain afinancial management system, prepare and furnish to the Bank financial reports, and have its financial statements audited. |Frequency :Yearly
